            . I live in Holborn. On Sunday, the 12th of August, I was returning home from Notting-hill, about four o'clock in the morning - I was taken is a fainting fit, and fell down about half a mile from Hyde-park corner; when I recovered I felt for my money, and missed the articles stated - Peter Hussey came to me, and I told him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-330-person2748">
                  PETER 
                  HUSSEY
               <interp inst="t18320906-330-person2748" type="surname" value="HUSSEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-330-person2748" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-330-person2748" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Ivory's-buildings, and am a coach painter. I was in the road, and saw the prosecutor in the kennel - I saw the prisoner and another man come up to him - one of them went up to him and the other stood in the centre of the road - I saw the prosecutor's pocket turned inside out; the prisoner and his companion ran off; I pursued them to the Edgware-road, and the officer took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-330-person2749">
                  DAVID 
                  DAVIS
