                  </persName>
             (Police-constable T 132). I stopped the prisoner, and found on him a silver sixpence, 1d., a knife, key, and a tobacco-stopper; the other was not detained.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had no place to go to; I had been into the park, and laid down till four o'clock - I got over the wall, and saw this man asleep in a kennel - I went to awake him; I did not disturb him - I sang out Halloo! I saw his pocket turned out, and these things by the side of it, and I took them up.</p>
